            <title>[SPARK-19306] Fix inconsistent state in DiskBlockObjectWriter when exception occurred</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19306</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;DiskBlockObjectWriter&lt;/tt&gt;, when some errors happened during writing, it will call &lt;tt&gt;revertPartialWritesAndClose&lt;/tt&gt;, if this method again failed due to some hardware issues like out of disk, it will throw exception without resetting the state of this writer, also skipping the revert. So here propose to fix this issue to offer user a chance to recover from such issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
